pi.reductions

Interface Reduction<E>


  • public interface Reduction<E>
    Defines a reduction and includes a range of built-in reductions (only a few common ones are implemented). Users may also define their own by implementing this interface.
    Author:
    Vikas Added reductions for minus, multi, bitOR, bitXOR, bitAND; added Float, Short, Byte reductions, Nasser Giacaman, Oliver Sinnen

    • Method Detail

      • reduce

        E reduce(E first,
         E second)
        Specifies a reduction as defined by 2 elements into 1. The reduction must obey the following 2 constraints:
        • Associative: the order of evaluating the reduction makes no difference, and
        • Commutative: the order of the thread-local values makes no difference.
        Parameters:
        first - The first element in the reduction.
        second - The second element in the reduction.
        Returns:
        The result of reducing first with second.
